>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Relativity/Tensors/Elab.html#TensorSpecies.Tensor.stringToTerm\"><span class=\"name\">TensorSpecies</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tensor</span>.<span class=\"name\">stringToTerm</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">str</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#String\">String</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Term/TermElabM.html#Lean.Elab.Term.TermElabM\">Lean.Elab.TermElabM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Meta/Defs.html#Lean.Syntax.Term\">Lean.Term</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The construction of an expression corresponding to the type of a given string once parsed. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Relativity/Tensors/Elab.html#TensorSpecies.Tensor.stringToTerm","kind":"def","line":200,"name":"TensorSpecies.Tensor.stringToTerm","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L200-L208"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Relativity/Tensors/Elab.html#TensorSpecies.Tensor.getPermutation\"><span class=\"name\">TensorSpecies</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tensor</span>.<span class=\"name\">getPermutation</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">l1 </span><span class=\"fn\">l2</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> (<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TSyntax\">Lean.TSyntax</a> <span class=\"fn\">`indexExpr</span>)</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Term/TermElabM.html#Lean.Elab.Term.TermElabM\">Lean.Elab.TermElabM</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given two lists of indices, all of which are indent,\nreturns the `List (ℕ)` representing the how one list\npermutes into the other. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Relativity/Tensors/Elab.html#TensorSpecies.Tensor.getPermutation","kind":"def","line":186,"name":"TensorSpecies.Tensor.getPermutation","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L186-L198"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Relativity/Tensors/Elab.html#TensorSpecies.Tensor.contrListAdjust\"><span class=\"name\">TensorSpecies</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tensor</span>.<span class=\"name\">contrListAdjust</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">l</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> (<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> (<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Adjusts a list `List (ℕ × ℕ)` by subtracting from each natural number the number\nof elements before it in the list which are less than itself. This is used\nto form a list of pairs which can be used for contracting indices. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Relativity/Tensors/Elab.html#TensorSpecies.Tensor.contrListAdjust","kind":"def","line":170,"name":"TensorSpecies.Tensor.contrListAdjust","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L170-L178"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Relativity/Tensors/Elab.html#TensorSpecies.Tensor.toPairs\"><span class=\"name\">TensorSpecies</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tensor</span>.<span class=\"name\">toPairs</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">l</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> (<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Takes a list and puts consecutive elements into pairs.\ne.g. [0, 1, 2, 3] becomes [(0, 1), (2, 3)]. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Relativity/Tensors/Elab.html#TensorSpecies.Tensor.toPairs","kind":"def","line":162,"name":"TensorSpecies.Tensor.toPairs","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L162-L168"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Relativity/Tensors/Elab.html#TensorSpecies.Tensor.withoutContrEval\"><span class=\"name\">TensorSpecies</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tensor</span>.<span class=\"name\">withoutContrEval</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">ind</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> (<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TSyntax\">Lean.TSyntax</a> <span class=\"fn\">`indexExpr</span>)</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Term/TermElabM.html#Lean.Elab.Term.TermElabM\">Lean.Elab.TermElabM</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> (<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TSyntax\">Lean.TSyntax</a> <span class=\"fn\">`indexExpr</span>))</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The list of indices after contraction or evaluation. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Relativity/Tensors/Elab.html#TensorSpecies.Tensor.withoutContrEval","kind":"def","line":157,"name":"TensorSpecies.Tensor.withoutContrEval","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L157-L160"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Relativity/Tensors/Elab.html#TensorSpecies.Tensor.getContrPos\"><span class=\"name\">TensorSpecies</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tensor</span>.<span class=\"name\">getContrPos</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">ind</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> (<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TSyntax\">Lean.TSyntax</a> <span class=\"fn\">`indexExpr</span>)</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Term/TermElabM.html#Lean.Elab.Term.TermElabM\">Lean.Elab.TermElabM</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> (<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>))</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For list of `indexExpr` e.g. `[α, 3, β, α, 2, γ]`, `getContrPos`\nfirst removes all indices which are numbers (e.g. `[α, β, α, γ]`).\nIt then outputs pairs `(a, b)` in `ℕ × ℕ` of positions of this list with `a < b`\nsuch that the index at `a` is equal to the index at `b`. It checks whether or not\nan element is contracted more then once. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Relativity/Tensors/Elab.html#TensorSpecies.Tensor.getContrPos","kind":"def","line":143,"name":"TensorSpecies.Tensor.getContrPos","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L143-L155"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Relativity/Tensors/Elab.html#TensorSpecies.Tensor.getEvalPos\"><span class=\"name\">TensorSpecies</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tensor</span>.<span class=\"name\">getEvalPos</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">ind</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> (<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TSyntax\">Lean.TSyntax</a> <span class=\"fn\">`indexExpr</span>)</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Term/TermElabM.html#Lean.Elab.Term.TermElabM\">Lean.Elab.TermElabM</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> (<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>))</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For list of `indexExpr` e.g. `[α, 3, β, 2, γ]`, `getEvalPos`\nreturns a list of pairs `ℕ × ℕ` related to indices which are numbers.\nThe second element of each pair is the number corresponding to that index.\nThe first element is the position of that number in the list of indices when\nall other numbered indices before it are removed. Thus for the example given\n`getEvalPos` outputs `[(1, 3), (2, 2)]`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Relativity/Tensors/Elab.html#TensorSpecies.Tensor.getEvalPos","kind":"def","line":130,"name":"TensorSpecies.Tensor.getEvalPos","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L130-L141"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Relativity/Tensors/Elab.html#TensorSpecies.Tensor.evalAdjustPos\"><span class=\"name\">TensorSpecies</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tensor</span>.<span class=\"name\">evalAdjustPos</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">l</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Adjusts a list `List ℕ` by subtracting from each natural number the number\nof elements before it in the list which are less than itself. This is used\nto form a list of pairs which can be used for evaluating indices. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Relativity/Tensors/Elab.html#TensorSpecies.Tensor.evalAdjustPos","kind":"def","line":120,"name":"TensorSpecies.Tensor.evalAdjustPos","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L120-L128"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Relativity/Tensors/Elab.html#TensorSpecies.Tensor.indexToDual\"><span class=\"name\">TensorSpecies</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tensor</span>.<span class=\"name\">indexToDual</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">stx</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Syntax\">Lean.Syntax</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Bool which is true if an index is of the form τ(i) that is, to be dualed. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Relativity/Tensors/Elab.html#TensorSpecies.Tensor.indexToDual","kind":"def","line":108,"name":"TensorSpecies.Tensor.indexToDual","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L108-L112"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Relativity/Tensors/Elab.html#TensorSpecies.Tensor.indexPosEq\"><span class=\"name\">TensorSpecies</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tensor</span>.<span class=\"name\">indexPosEq</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TSyntax\">Lean.TSyntax</a> <span class=\"fn\">`indexExpr</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a hr